#Logical Model
Tables will be: Clients, Dogs, Walks, Payments
-Client to Dogs may have a one to many relationship because one client may have more than one dog
-Dog and Walk may have a one to many relationship because one dog can have many walks
-Client to Payments may have more than one dog because one client may have many payments
-A many to many relationship could be between walks and dogs since Lana may walk multiple dogs
4.)We came to the conclusion that we would need to add a junction table, so that way we would have a many to many relationship. We all had the same concept and ideas the only difference was depending on what questions we asked AI. We all got the same primary and foreign keys.
b).Some question we asked, what if Lana walks more then one dog at a time and it gave a feed back of junction table to help with that. That was the only difference and some different details under the categories. The junction table (walk_dog) is used to resolve the many-to-many relationship between walk_dog and walks, allowing multiple dogs to be assigned to a single walk. 
